ENTRY            C0228   20260122   20260325   20260325       C254
SUBENT        C0228001   20260122   20260325   20260325       C254
BIB                 12         29
INSTITUTE  (2FR CSN)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,165,405,1971)
           #doi:10.1016/0375-9474(71)90769-X
AUTHOR     (P.Fontes,C.Perron,J.Lestringuez,F.Yiou,R.Bernas)
TITLE      Production cross sections of lithium and beryllium
           isotopes in C-12 by high-energy protons and alpha
           particles
FACILITY   (SYNCY,2FR PAR) for alpha and 155 MeV Protons
           (SYNCY,2ZZZCER) for 600 MeV protons
SAMPLE     High purity graphite pieces: 20*6*1 mm in size.
METHOD     (INTB)
DETECTOR   (MAGSP)
INC-SPECT  For proton irradiations targets consisted in stacks of
           10 to 12 graphite pieces wrapped in a 0.02 mm thick
           aluminium foil: this arrangement corresponds to a
           total energy loss of about 10 MeV at 155 MeV and 3 MeV
           at 600 mev; for alpha-particle irradiations: only 4
           graphite slabs were used, mean energy of alpha-
           particles in each of the four sheets were 137, 126,
           114 and 100 MeV.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Accuracy of +- 10 % included statistical
           errors and uncertainty resulting from mass-spectrometer
           discrimination.
STATUS     (TABLE,,P.Fontes+,J,NP/A,165,405,1971)
            Tables 1,2 in reference
HISTORY    (19870420C)
           (20260121A) OS. Major data correction in sub.9,
            STATUS added, FACILITY updated, other BIB updates,
            converted to lower and upper case
ENDBIB              29
